---
allowed-tools: Read, Write, Bash, Glob, Grep
description: Upgrade .claude/ to the latest claude-bootstrap templates, preserving agent memory
---

Upgrade this project's Claude Code configuration to the latest templates.

## Step 1: Protect agent memory

Read `.claude/agent-memory/` to understand what accumulated knowledge exists —
this context informs the upgrade report but is **never modified**.

```bash
ls -la .claude/agent-memory/ 2>/dev/null && \
  find .claude/agent-memory -name "*.md" | head -20 || echo "No agent memory found"
```

Report what memory was found (e.g., "planner has 3 memory files, qa has 2").

## Step 2: Inventory current .claude/

```bash
find .claude -type f | grep -v agent-memory | grep -v settings.local.json | sort
```

Identify:
- Which standard commands exist vs which are missing
- Which standard agents exist vs which are missing
- Any custom commands or agents (not in the standard set — preserve these untouched)

Standard commands: prime, plan, implement, validate, commit, create-pr, review-pr,
prd, rca, check-ignores, create-command, create-rules, design, upgrade

Standard agents: planner, code-reviewer, qa, frontend, design, backend, database, devops

## Step 3: Extract current placeholder values

Read existing generated files to recover the project-specific values:

```bash
# From commands
cat .claude/commands/validate.md 2>/dev/null
cat .claude/commands/implement.md 2>/dev/null
cat .claude/agents/planner.md 2>/dev/null
cat .claude/agents/frontend.md 2>/dev/null
cat .claude/settings.json 2>/dev/null
cat CLAUDE.md 2>/dev/null
```

Build a values map by reading what was substituted:
- `LANGUAGE` — from agent system prompts ("You are a senior ... for a X / Y project")
- `FRAMEWORK` — same source
- `PACKAGE_MANAGER` — from settings.json permissions ("Bash(pnpm run:*)")
- `LINT_COMMAND` — from validate.md or implement.md
- `TYPECHECK_COMMAND` — from validate.md or implement.md
- `BUILD_COMMAND` — from validate.md
- `TEST_COMMAND` — from validate.md or settings.json hooks
- `LINTER` — from code-reviewer.md
- `TEST_FRAMEWORK` — from code-reviewer.md or qa.md
- `PROJECT_NAME` — from CLAUDE.md heading
- `GITHUB_ISSUES_ENABLED` — check if qa.md contains a "## GitHub Issues" section

## Step 4: Find skill templates

```bash
ls ~/.claude/skills/claude-bootstrap/assets/templates/ 2>/dev/null || \
ls ~/.claude/skills/*/assets/templates/ 2>/dev/null | head -5
```

If found, read templates from that path.
If not found, use the template content you have in context from SKILL.md.

## Step 5: Present upgrade plan

Show a clear summary before making any changes:

```
📋 Upgrade plan for [PROJECT_NAME]:

  Commands to update:
    ✏️  prd.md        → SDD structure (sections 1-2)
    ✏️  plan.md       → SDD structure (sections 4-5)
    ✏️  implement.md  → SDD-aware flow
    ✏️  prime.md      → SDD scanning on startup
    ✏️  design.md     → contributes SDD section 3
    ➕  upgrade.md    → this command (add for future upgrades)

  Agents to update:
    ✏️  planner.md    → writes to SDD format
    ➕  design.md     → new (frontend detected: [FRAMEWORK])

  CLAUDE.md:
    ➕  ## Specs section (append only — existing content untouched)

  settings.json:
    ➕  Bash(gh issue:*) permission (if not present)

  Custom files (preserved untouched):
    🔒  [list any custom commands/agents found in Step 2]

  Protected (never modified):
    🔒  .claude/agent-memory/     ([N] files — [list agents with memory])
    🔒  .claude/settings.local.json

Ask for confirmation before proceeding.
```

## Step 6: Apply updates

**Commands** — Re-generate each outdated command filling in extracted values.
Overwrite the file entirely; commands are stateless instruction text.

**Agents** — Update surgically:
- Replace the system prompt header (first paragraph after frontmatter) if it changed
- Update or add specific sections (e.g., add `## GitHub Issues` to qa.md if enabled)
- Preserve `memory: project` frontmatter if already present
- Never modify the `## Memory` section content — it may contain project-specific customizations
- Preserve any sections not present in the standard template (user additions)

**CLAUDE.md** — Only append sections that don't already exist.
Check with `grep "## Specs" CLAUDE.md` before appending.

**settings.json** — Merge new entries into `permissions.allow` without removing existing ones.
Add new hooks only if the hook event/matcher combination doesn't already exist.

**Never touch:**
- `.claude/agent-memory/` — accumulated knowledge from all past sessions
- `.claude/settings.local.json` — personal overrides
- Any file not in the standard template set

## Step 7: Report

```
✅ Upgrade complete!

  Updated:    [list of files changed]
  Added:      [list of new files]
  Skipped:    [list of files already up to date]
  Preserved:  .claude/agent-memory/ ([N] files intact)

Agent memory summary:
  [agent]: [N] memory files — [brief description of what's stored]
```
